HEADWORD: Deuterocanonical
<hw>Deu`ter*o*ca*non"ic*al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>deu`teros</grk> second + E. <ets>canonical</ets>.]</ety>
<def>Pertaining to a second canon, or ecclesiastical writing of inferior
authority; -- said of the Apocrypha, certain Epistles, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

